Harness notes:
- Rodney 0.4.0 does NOT have an `eval` subcommand. All JS probes used `uvx rodney js <expr>`.
- The `rodney-capture.sh` helper calls the non-existent `eval` subcommand, so viewport sizing in
  that script is non-functional with the installed Rodney version. For probes and screenshots we
  set the viewport with:
    uvx rodney js "(() => { window.resizeTo(W, H);
                           document.documentElement.style.width='${W}px';
                           document.documentElement.style.height='${H}px';
                           return 'viewport-set'; })()"
- For the runtime checks the page must first boot webR/Pyodide (≈15 s) and load a lesson so the
  editor has a non-empty document.

=== Setup for runtime checks (both targets) ===
For each target, after page open and ~15 s wait for interpreter boot:
  await window.__bt.ready;
  await window.__bt.selectLesson(0);
  const ed = window.__bt.editorView;
  ed.focus();
  ed.dispatch({ changes: { from: 0, to: ed.state.doc.length, insert: 'f(x)' } });
  ed.dispatch({ selection: { anchor: 1 } });

